@description.name: @description
@description.body: An upload widget implementation capable of holding multiple upload buttons and upload fields. Each upload form creates an iframe which is used as a target for form submit.

@param.name: @param
@param.body: encoding {String} encoding for from submission. This is an instantiation only parameter and defaults to multipart/form-data
@param.description: encoding for from submission. This is an instantiation only parameter and defaults to multipart/form-data

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The name which is assigned to the form

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The url which is used for form submission.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The target which is used for form submission.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: The owning object

@description.name: @description
@description.body: {String} The ID of the object.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Create a hidden iframe which is used as target for the form submission. Don't need a src attribute, if it was set to javascript:void we get an insecure objects error in IE.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: replace the widgets content element with a form element so that we can then send the stuff away.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Add parameters as hidden fields to the form.

@param.name: @param

@param.description: value attribute of the created element ({@link #value}).

@param.body: id {String} identifier of the parameter to add.
@param.description: identifier of the parameter to add.

@description.name: @description

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Send the form via the submit method. Target defaults to the self created iframe.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: clear the form

@description.name: @description

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {DOMWindow} The DOM window object of the iframe.
@return.description: The DOM window object of the iframe.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Get the DOM document object of the target iframe.

@return.body: {DOMDocument} The DOM document object of the iframe.
@return.description: The DOM document object of the iframe.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Get the HTML body element of the target iframe.

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {Element} The DOM node of the body element of the iframe.
@return.description: The DOM node of the body element of the iframe.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Get the target iframe Element.

@return.description: The DOM element of the iframe.

@description.name: @description

@return.description: The text response of the submit.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Get the HTML content of the target iframe.

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {String} The html response of the submit.
@return.description: The html response of the submit.

@description.name: @description
@description.body: Get the XML content of the target iframe. This is a hack for now because I didn't find a way to send XML via the iframe response. In the resulting text all occurences of the < and > entities are replaces by < and > and the Text is then parsed into a XML-Document instance.

@return.name: @return
@return.body: {Document} The XML response of the submit.
@return.description: The XML response of the submit.
